  "notes_sections": [
    "``s`` is the shape parameter: the standard deviation of the underlying normal distribution. It is the first positional argument, ahead of ``loc`` and ``scale``, matching SciPy's ``lognorm`` signature. Each public method deducts ``1 * numel(input)`` FLOPs from the active budget."
  ],
